  "prompt": "What colours complement amber?",
  "response": "Amber is a warm, golden-orange color that can be complemented by a variety of other colors. Here are some options that work well with amber:\n\n1. **Blues**: Various shades of blue, from light sky blue to deep navy, create a soothing and balanced contrast with amber. Blue is on the opposite side of the color wheel, making it a complementary color to amber.\n\n2. **Greens**: Earthy greens, such as olive or forest green, can harmonize beautifully with amber, creating a natural and calming palette.\n\n3. **Purples**: Lavender or deeper purples can add a touch of elegance and sophistication when paired with amber.\n\n4. **Neutrals**: Colors like beige, cream, and gray can provide a subtle and versatile backdrop that allows amber to stand out.\n\n5. **Browns**: Various shades of brown, from light tan to dark chocolate, can enhance the warmth and richness of amber, creating a cozy and inviting atmosphere.\n\n6. **Whites**: Crisp white can make amber pop, providing a fresh and clean contrast.\n\nWhen choosing colors to complement amber, consider the mood and style you want to achieve. Whether you're looking for a vibrant contrast or a more harmonious blend, these color combinations can help you create a balanced and visually appealing palette.",
